  "local_port": 40038,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that offer a floating lookup or overlay feature, allowing you to look up words anywhere on your phone without needing to open the app. Here are a few options you can consider:\n\n### 1. **Google Translate**\nGoogle Translate offers a feature called \"Tap to Translate\" which allows you to copy text from any app and instantly translate it without leaving the app.\n\n**How to Use:**\n- Open Google Translate app.\n- Go to Settings > Tap to Translate and turn it on.\n- When you see a word you want to look up, copy it.\n- A Google Translate bubble will appear, tap on it to see the translation.\n\n### 2. **Microsoft Translator**\nMicrosoft Translator also provides an overlay feature that lets you select text from any app and translate it instantly.\n\n**How to Use:**\n- Open Microsoft Translator app.\n- Go to Settings and enable the \"Translate Tap\" feature.\n- When you see a word you want to look up, long-press on it and select \"Translate with Microsoft Translator.\"\n\n### 3. **Dictionary Lingua.ly**\nLingua.ly Dictionary is another app that offers a floating widget which you can use to look up words directly from other apps.\n\n**How to Use:**\n- Open Lingua.ly Dictionary app.\n- Enable the floating widget from the app's settings.\n- Drag the widget over any text you want to look up.\n\n### 4. **Floating Dictionary**\nFloating Dictionary is an app specifically designed to provide a floating widget for looking up words without leaving the current app.\n\n**How to Use:**\n- Install and open Floating Dictionary.\n- Enable the floating icon from the app's settings.\n- Use the floating icon to select and look up words on your screen.\n\n### 5. **Blue Dictionary**\nBlue Dictionary is another tool that provides a floating bubble for quick word lookups.\n\n**How to Use:**\n- Install and open Blue Dictionary.\n- Enable the floating bubble from the app's settings.\n- Use the bubble to select and look up words on any screen.\n\nThese apps vary in their features and user interfaces, so you might want to try a few to see which one works best for your needs. Always check the permissions and privacy policies of any app before installing to ensure you're comfortable with the data they collect.",
